# Context Pilot — Caddy reverse proxy + private-CA TLS (tls internal).
#
# "Tout local, rien sur le web": this box has NO public DNS and NO public ACME.
# Caddy terminates all TLS with its built-in CA (`tls internal`); the root is
# distributed to clients out-of-band (see the IT maintenance console on :9090).
#
# IMPORTANT: this file is a BOOTSTRAP fallback only. The orchestrator REGENERATES
# it at boot and on every identity/finalize change — rendering explicit name/IP
# site addresses, the cockpit on :443 once provisioned, and the :80→:443 redirect
# (see crates/cp-orchestrator/src/transport/maint/caddy.rs). The orchestrator
# starts before Caddy (procd START 95 vs 96), so by the time Caddy reads this it
# has usually been replaced. Until then we serve only the maintenance plane.
{
	# LAN appliance: private CA only, never reach out to public ACME.
	auto_https disable_redirects
}

# IT maintenance plane — reachable on the LAN before the box is named.
# Caddy fronts the public :9090 and proxies to the orchestrator's loopback
# maintenance listener (CP_MAINT_PORT=9191, CP_MAINT_BIND=127.0.0.1).
:9090 {
	tls internal
	reverse_proxy 127.0.0.1:9191
}

# The product cockpit (:443) and the :80→:443 redirect are intentionally ABSENT
# here: an unprovisioned box must not serve the cockpit. The orchestrator adds
# those blocks only after `finalize` flips the box to provisioned.
